[I] A faster way to navigate your filesystem

[T] zoxide is a smarter cd command, inspired by z and autojump. It remembers
[T] which directories you use most frequently, so you can "jump" to them in
[T] just a few keystrokes - zoxide works on all major shells.

[U] https://github.com/ajeetdsouza/zoxide

[A] Zoxide Authors
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

